      "summary": "Paani is a humanitarian organization that addresses the global water crisis by providing <cite id=\"1\">sustainable clean water and relief</cite> to underserved communities. While primarily focused on Pakistan, the organization has expanded its reach to <cite id=\"2\">include programs in Iraq</cite>. Paani operates with a high degree of financial transparency, earning a <cite id=\"3\">91.75/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>. In 2023, the organization reported <cite id=\"4\">total revenue of $2,547,511</cite>, reflecting a significant growth trajectory with a <cite id=\"5\">3-year revenue CAGR of 24.7%</cite>. The charity's model is built on direct service delivery, ranging from <cite id=\"6\">deep water wells to orphan and famine relief</cite>. For Muslim donors, Paani offers a <cite id=\"7\">verified Zakat-eligible giving platform</cite> that supports the poor and needy. The organization maintains <cite id=\"8\">5.9 months of working capital</cite>, ensuring it can sustain operations during funding fluctuations. Despite its growth, Paani maintains a lean administrative structure, reporting <cite id=\"9\">$0.00 spent to raise every $1</cite> in its baseline efficiency metrics.",
